%
% Passing criteria (Mumbai University pattern):
%   CIE  >= 18 (out of 40)
%   ESE  >= 24 (out of 60)
%   Both conditions must be satisfied to pass a subject.
%
% Grace rule:
%   If exactly 1 subject is failed AND grace needed <= 6 marks,
%   grace is applied.
%
% SGPA grading (10-point scale):
%   O  (Outstanding) : >= 91 → 10
%   A+ (Excellent)   : 81-90 → 9
%   A  (Very Good)   : 71-80 → 8
%   B+ (Good)        : 61-70 → 7
%   B  (Above Avg)   : 55-60 → 6
%   C  (Average)     : 50-54 → 5
%   P  (Pass)        : 40-49 → 4
%   F  (Fail)        : < 40  → 0
% ============================================================

